<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n54120h"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n54" href="#n54120h">N54 (VI.B.45)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n54all.htm#n54120h"> 120(h)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> K laments more death of / friend,</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">The <mark>manifestations of grief</mark> were quite different when Yel Yuan <mark>one of his favourite disciples</mark> died for then his usual self-possession deserted him and he grieved so excessively that some of the more outspoken of the remaining disciples remonstrated with him as he had done with his son for grieving so long over the death of his mother. <small> Carl Crow, <a name="CCMK" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#CCMK"><cite title="source">Master Kung. The Story of Confucius</cite></a> (Sep 1937) 296</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
